{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox officeholder | name = Abdulla Jihad | office = 6th [[Vice President of the Maldives]] | native_name = | image = | caption = | predecessor = [[Ahmed Adeeb]] | president = [[Abdulla Yameen]] | party = [[Progressive Party of Maldives]] | office1 = Minister of Finance & Treasury | Predecessor = Mohamed Shihab | Successor = Ahmed Munawwar | birth_name = Abdulla Jihad | birth_place = [[Thinadhoo (Gaafu Dhaalu Atoll)]][[Maldives]] | religion = [[Islam]] | term_start = 22 June 2016 | term_end = | term_start1 = 17 November 2013 | term_end1 = 22 June 2016 }}
'''Abdulla Jihad''' is the 6th Vice President of [[Maldives]]. Prior to his appointment on 22 June 2016, he served as the Minister of Finance & Treasury.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.presidencymaldives.gov.mv/Index.aspx?lid=11&dcid=16901|title=The President's Office - His Excellency Abdulla Jihad sworn in as Vice President|website=www.presidencymaldives.gov.mv|access-date=2016-06-22}}</ref>
== Early career and family life == Abdulla Jihad was born and raised in [[Thinadhoo (Gaafu Dhaalu Atoll)|Thinadhoo]] of South Huvadhoo Atoll.
